snippet: While scientists are excited about what the experiment may yield, they are also concerned about the absence of future moon voyages on NASA’s schedule.
abstract: Final moon mission on National Aeronautics and Space Administration's current schedule is a small, unmanned spacecraft that will study moon dust and lunar atmosphere; mission elates scientists but highlights political questions about what NASA should do next in the absence of future moon voyages on the agency's schedule.
lead_paragraph: While scientists are excited about what the experiment may yield, they are also concerned about the absence of future moon voyages on NASA’s schedule.

headline.main: New Moon Probe Raises Questions About What to Do Next in Space
